summary: This document is an email chain from October 11, 2019, regarding the approval of travel for FBI agents to conduct victim briefings and interviews in Florida as part of the ongoing Epstein investigation. The travel is for agents to meet with victims in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast.

persons.name: SA Young
persons.context: Special Agent in New York who submitted the initial travel request for the Epstein victim briefing and interviews in Florida.

persons.name: SSA
persons.role: Supervisory Special Agent, Violent Crime Section
persons.context: Supervisory Special Agent from the Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit who approved the travel request and requested the case number to process the authorization.

connections.description: SA Young submitted a travel request to the SSA for approval, indicating a supervisory or reporting relationship within the FBI's Violent Crime Section.

events.title: Epstein Victim Briefing and Interviews in Florida
events.description: FBI agents planned to travel to Florida for a victim briefing in Miami and to conduct victim and witness interviews in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast as part of the ongoing Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The FBI's Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit was actively investigating Epstein-related cases as of October 2019.
Travel was approved for FBI agents to conduct victim briefings and interviews in multiple Florida cities.
The travel request involved four agents for the Miami portion and two agents for the West Palm Beach/Palm Coast portion.
The total estimated cost for the travel was $6,263.50.
The document indicates ongoing victim engagement and witness interviews in the Epstein investigation post-Epstein's death.
